                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The text was copied in an <term type="script">upright ogival
                                        majuscule</term> script, in dark brown ink, with breathings
                                    and accents, and some expansion of letters. There are deletions
                                    by erasure and correction by overwriting.</p>
                                <p>The horizontal stroke for <hi rend="italic">nu</hi> appears at
                                    the end of lines. Mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent.
                                    Breathings are sometimes omitted. There is decorative use of the
                                    double dot. When it appears on the first letter of a word, the
                                    breathing is omitted. The word υἱός appears on occasion
                                    uncontracted.</p>
                                <p>
                           <hi rend="italic">Psi</hi> appears with both diagonal and
                                    horizontal bars. The ligatures ΑΥ, ΗΝ, ΜΗ, ΟΥ, ΤΗ are
                                    present.</p>
                                <p>Headings and lection information are written in <term type="script">Alexandrine majuscule</term> script, in red
                                    and brown ink. There are deletions by strikethrough. Breathings
                                    are both angular and round. </p>
                                <p>The only punctuation to appear is the middle point.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <musicNotation>The text is supplied with ekphonetic notation in red
                            ink.</musicNotation>

                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="colInit">Lections begin with large initials in red ink,
                                with some ornamentation. Sections of headings begin with smaller,
                                simpler initials in red ink.</decoNote>

                            <decoNote type="plainInit">Sub-sections of the main text are marked by
                                simple, enlarged initials in brown ink.</decoNote>

                            <decoNote type="lineFill">The end of a lection is accompanied by a
                                line-filler in red ink (<locus from="3v" to="3v">f.
                                3v</locus>).</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>

                        <additions>There are corrections and alterations by a later hand, in black
                            ink. A modern chapter and verse reference has been added for the
                            beginning of the text. The fragment is marked with the current classmark
                            and the former classmark T.2.</additions>

                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding calendar="gregorian" when="2019">
                                <p> The fragment has a modern card binding reinforced with cloth
                                    inside the spine.</p>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
